00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,560
{\an8}Mook!

2
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,840
{\an8}You've got a nosebleed.

3
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,480
{\an8}- Hold on.
- Wait, Mr. Thee!

4
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:09,280
{\an8}My friends are making fun of me.

5
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,720
{\an8}They say my mom's going to remarry.

6
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,880
{\an8}I don't want her to remarry.

7
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:21,040
{\an8}<i>I don't want my mom to be sad.</i>

8
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:24,920
{\an8}Because I got to see
just how great the love

9
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,960
{\an8}Mook has for her daughter is.

10
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:31,080
{\an8}I want to protect their feelings.

11
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,760
{\an8}Well, I hope you haven't forgotten

12
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,480
{\an8}that you already have someone.

13
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,560
TOR'S GARAGE

14
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:54,040
MR. PAT

15
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:05,720
Boss, my car broke down at The One.

16
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,400
Okay. See you soon, Boss.

17
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:19,000
I'm leaving my car here.

18
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,560
Mr. Pat will take care of it.

19
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,240
We brought this for you.

20
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,440
Next time, you don't have
to bring anything.

21
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,720
We're already happy to see you two.

22
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,480
- Have a seat.
- Yes.

23
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:14,080
Thank you for taking good care
of our daughter, Top.

24
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,320
- My pleasure.
- How about you, Ploy?

25
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,480
How have you been?

26
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,320
Did you trouble him in any way?

27
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,880
Not at all.

28
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:28,640
She's a really good wife,
and she takes great care of me.

29
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,560
If I'd known being married to her
would be this great,

30
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,400
I would've had Pa talk to you sooner.

31
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,360
That's great. Keep your love strong.

32
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:43,000
Help each other out when in need.

33
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,560
And you too, Ploy.

34
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,480
Take good care of him, okay?

35
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:49,560
Remember to forgive each other,

36
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,840
and don't forget
to give me a grandchild soon.

37
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,320
Of course.

38
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,240
How are you?

39
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,640
Who did this to you, Preaw?

40
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,000
Can you tell me?

41
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:39,000
Even if I told you,
there's nothing you can do, Khim.

42
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:48,200
After all, you're one
of Top's victims too.

43
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,880
So… you knew?

44
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,360
Yeah.

45
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:04,920
I saw your video on his phone.

46
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:26,000
At first, he was a really good man.

47
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,720
He spoiled me in every way.

48
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:33,480
But before long, he changed…

49
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:39,800
from someone good to a complete monster.

50
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,400
He threatened me

51
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:52,920
that if I told anyone he beat me,

52
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,320
he'd leak the video he secretly took of me
to expose me online.

53
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:02,400
At first, I thought it was just a threat.

54
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:07,040
But it turned out
that scumbag would actually do it.

55
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:20,000
Did you know he was married?

56
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,200
At first, I didn't know,

57
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:27,000
but then I found out,
so I broke up with him.

58
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,360
He wouldn't let me.

59
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,400
And he even told me

60
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,840
it's not just me and his wife.

61
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,760
There are other girls too.

62
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:41,920
From then on, he started beating me,

63
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:45,600
threatening me, and abusing me.

64
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,320
It's exactly like what you've heard.

65
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,400
That's how that scumbag threatened me too.

66
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,160
You have to be careful, Khim.

67
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,400
He's a very scary guy.

68
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,760
He's got videos
of every girl he's slept with.

69
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:23,200
He'd do anything
to make everyone obey his orders.

70
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:19,560
PLOY

71
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:46,360
KHIM

72
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,840
<i>Don't you dare tell anyone</i>
<i>about what's going on at home,</i>

73
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,360
<i>or you'll regret it.</i>

74
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,360
Hello? Ploy!

75
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,320
Hello. What's up, Khim?

76
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,120
How have you been lately?

77
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,640
I haven't seen you in a while.

78
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,080
Are you okay?

79
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:23,880
I'm…

80
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,600
I'm doing alright.

81
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,800
How are you?

82
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,440
I'm doing alright too.

83
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:41,960
How come I can't get hold of you lately?

84
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,520
Busy with work?

85
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,280
Yeah, work's been busy.

86
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:54,360
I haven't had a chance to talk to anyone.

87
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,480
<i>And also…</i>

88
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,120
Also what?

89
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,040
It's normal.

90
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,360
<i>I'm used to it now.</i>

91
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,400
Year-end closing times are always busy.

92
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,640
<i>Ploy.</i>

93
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,160
It's been a while.

94
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,960
Can we meet sometime?

95
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,000
Of course.

96
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,120
So, tomorrow, at our usual place?

97
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,040
<i>I miss you both.</i>

98
00:11:57,240 --> 00:12:00,080
Thank you for taking care of my car, Boss.

99
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,880
So you've thought it through?

100
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,280
Sorry?

101
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,160
Normally, if your car broke down,

102
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,120
you'd be able to handle it easily
on your own.

103
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,560
You never had to call me.

104
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:20,000
But this time, you wanted
to prove a point to Mr. Thee, right?

105
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,720
That's why you called me.

106
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,840
You sure know me well.

107
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:34,960
Well, it's probably the best way
to make him understand

108
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:39,840
that I've made my decision.

109
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:44,920
Yeah.

110
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:49,080
Let's go, honey. Mind your hand.

111
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,560
Mommy!

112
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,280
I'm back.

113
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:03,920
Good evening.

114
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,600
- Good evening.
- Good evening, Uncle.

115
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,120
Mook's car broke down,
so I offered to drive her.

116
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,320
I see. Thank you very much.

117
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,880
Why don't you have dinner with us?

118
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:14,520
That's alright.

119
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,560
I'm hungry. Let's go eat.

120
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,560
Sure.

121
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,560
Thanks again, Boss.

122
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,480
Of course.

123
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:26,840
- Good night, ma'am.
- Good night.

124
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:29,080
Say goodbye to Uncle Pat. Let's go.

125
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,480
- Let's eat.
- Good night.

126
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,680
Wash your hands first, okay?

127
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,040
Walk slowly, Kongkwan!

128
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,200
Bye.

129
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:42,440
Wait for your mommy!

130
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,440
Yes, Mom.

131
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:15,200
What's up?

132
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:20,800
- Hey!
- Could be the starter or the battery.

133
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,760
You know, how about I drive you?

134
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:26,400
I'll have Mr. Pitak take care of your car.

135
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:28,120
Thank you,

136
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,280
but no thank you.

137
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:52,200
Why am I thinking of him?

138
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:56,680
Stop thinking, Mook. Stop, stop, stop.

139
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:39,680
If you're making me apologize to her,
you can just leave,

140
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,280
because I'd never do that.

141
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,160
But you started it all, Prao!

142
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:46,120
You almost destroyed my company.

143
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,000
You're lucky Mr. Thee didn't sue.

144
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,320
It's still just "almost".

145
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,760
It's not destroyed yet, the way I want it!

146
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,360
- Prao!
- What?!

147
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:57,280
Can you two stop fighting?

148
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,280
Pun.

149
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:06,400
I see you and Mommy fighting all the time.

150
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,520
Why do you have to fight?

151
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,440
Don't you love each other anymore?

152
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,120
He's the one who stopped loving me.

153
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,000
Seriously, Prao?

154
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,240
Can't you see our son's upset?

155
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,880
Mommy and Daddy
were having a little disagreement,

156
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,440
so we had to settle it.

157
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:43,840
It's like when I have a fight
with my friends, right?

158
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:48,160
My teacher told us to hold hands
and apologize to each other,

159
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,880
so that we wouldn't fight again.

160
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,359
I'll try my best.

161
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:18,000
Hey. How about this?

162
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,240
We will take you on a vacation.

163
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:24,200
- It's been a while, hasn't it?
- Really?

164
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:27,240
Are we really going on vacation?

165
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,760
- You're not lying to me, right, Mommy?
- No.

166
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,920
Is it true, Daddy?

167
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:30,760
THEE

168
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:33,720
<i>Are you coming out,</i>
<i>or do you want me to go inside?</i>

169
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,520
Why are you doing this? I--

170
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,520
Hey!

171
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,680
Can you stand still just for a minute?

172
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,560
Let me recharge my energy.

173
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,600
Did something happen?

174
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,320
I have a very important event coming up.

175
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,600
So I wanted your energy.

176
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,640
Thank you.

177
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:21,680
I'm okay now.

178
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,320
Are you sure

179
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,880
that you're okay?

180
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,360
Yes.

181
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,480
Go get some rest.

182
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:41,120
I've contacted the investor
who wanted to invest in our hotel.

183
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:44,880
He wanted to meet with you,
Mrs. Narin. Are you available?

184
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,520
We'd better decide soon.

185
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:57,440
With our situation,
we won't be able to cope for long.

186
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,440
Did he make any offers?

187
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:05,800
What type of investment is it going to be?

188
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:08,240
He wants as many of our shares

189
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:10,160
as we can sell him

190
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:13,520
because he's very eager
to invest in our hotel.

191
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,360
Who is he, Mr. Chadchai? Can you tell me?

192
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:20,920
I suggest you go speak to him yourself.

193
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:24,040
Okay.

194
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:28,240
I wanted to hear his comments anyway.

195
00:22:52,520 --> 00:22:53,560
Hi.

196
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:58,960
There's something off about you.

197
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:06,560
You two kept making fun of me,
so I tried a trendy makeup look.

198
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,800
Does it look good?

199
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,640
What about Mook? Isn't she coming?

200
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:19,160
She's kind of busy lately,
so she couldn't come.

201
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,200
I never got to see you
since you got married.

202
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:29,880
How's it been? Everything okay?

203
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,280
I'm okay.

204
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,800
I'm doing so fine.

205
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:38,840
Top's been really good to me.

206
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:43,240
Married life is actually not so bad.

207
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,880
I must've won the lottery,
like you both said.

208
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,200
<i>Did you hear?</i>

209
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:52,400
Preaw submitted a resignation letter.

210
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:54,320
I just visited her.

211
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,320
She didn't say anything about quitting.

212
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:01,040
She submitted it just a few days
before being hospitalized.

213
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:04,000
No one knows why, though.

214
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:07,200
I think it must've had
something to do with that guy.

215
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,400
I feel bad for her.

216
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:12,240
Her career was going well.

217
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,680
Ploy, I've got something to tell you.

218
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,880
{\an8}TOP

219
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:29,280
Hey, I just remembered
I have a date with Top.

220
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:31,160
Let's meet again soon. I'll call you.

221
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,640
Ploy! Ploy, Wait!

222
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,360
Opposite this house is like a slum.

223
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,520
Unacceptable.

224
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:50,920
Why buy a house so far from town
if it's going to be this sunny?

225
00:24:57,440 --> 00:25:01,040
You sure came a long way. Are you tired?

226
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:06,240
For me, it's no hassle,
but it really was a long way.

227
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:10,960
So, what brought you all the way here?

228
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,560
I'll be frank with you.

229
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:17,800
I wanted to warn you about how
your daughter's been behaving.

230
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:22,600
You must've seen the news
about your naughty daughter,

231
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:25,240
how she attracted those guys.

232
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:29,840
You know, it really
isn't any of my business,

233
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:32,720
but I came to warn you

234
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,680
because she's still my son's ex-wife

235
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:40,160
and my granddaughter's mom.

236
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:43,040
You are a mother too.

237
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:44,400
I'm sure you understand.

238
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:48,760
Actually, it's Mook's personal life,

239
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:52,720
and she's already divorced your son.

240
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,200
Also,

241
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:58,840
when Kuk did a bad thing
and cheated on her,

242
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,040
I never got involved.

243
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:05,400
So, I don't think
you should worry about her.

244
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,880
Just take good care of your son.

245
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:11,520
I see where she got her stubbornness from.

246
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:16,160
I just wanted to warn her
not to be so obnoxious.

247
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:19,920
If you won't do it for Kuk,
at least do it for Kongkwan!

248
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:23,280
I just don't want her to be embarrassed
to have a mom like that.

249
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,880
Even the door's sticking. Fix it sometime.

250
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,600
Whan told me you wanted to see me.

251
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:46,080
What's the matter?

252
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:49,360
Nothing.

253
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:53,360
I just wanted to ask
if I could take a couple days off.

254
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,720
Is there anything urgent planned?

255
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:57,440
You're the CEO here.

256
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:59,040
Why are you asking for my approval?

257
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,160
There's nothing urgent coming up.

258
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:08,200
There's just our campaign with The One.

259
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,400
I can handle it. You don't have to worry.

260
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,720
Prao wanted me
to take Poonpun on a vacation.

261
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:19,360
Really? Does that mean
you've worked things out?

262
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:22,000
It's still the same as always.

263
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:25,440
We barely got a few words in
before we started fighting.

264
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,320
What should I do, Mook?

265
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:38,480
I can't even deal
with my own problems, Boss.

266
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:45,080
But to be honest, in my case,

267
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:48,320
there was no way
we could go back to normal.

268
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:52,000
But in your case,

269
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:55,760
you two might still
be able to stay together.

270
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,840
Don't you think?

271
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,280
To be honest, Mook,

272
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,320
I'm only doing this for my son.

273
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:16,040
But when two people must stay together
because of a responsibility,

274
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,200
not because of love,

275
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,880
it just seems so fragile,

276
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:23,880
like it'll easily fall apart.

277
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:32,160
But in the end,
no matter how it turns out,

278
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:37,240
at least you'll have tried
your best for your son.

279
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:06,880
Where were you?

280
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,200
I was at work, of course.

281
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:12,200
I called your work.

282
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:14,240
They said you asked to leave early.

283
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:19,000
Why'd you have to call my work to check?

284
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:21,800
Why do you never respect me?

285
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,040
Don't change the topic.

286
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:27,680
I asked you, where were you today?

287
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:28,960
Give me that.

288
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:31,880
Top! That's mine!

289
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,800
Here's your milk, Mom.

290
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,400
Thank you, honey.

291
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:13,280
Is something wrong?

292
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,720
You seem a little stressed.

293
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:17,040
Mrs. Tiansee was here today.

294
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:20,120
Why was she here?

295
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:23,480
Did she say something
to make you feel bad?

296
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:27,400
Is it about the news?

297
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:29,360
I need to go talk to her tomorrow.

298
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:33,120
All this back-and-forth
won't do you any good.

299
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,680
Let's just leave her alone.

300
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:41,920
If she wants to be spiteful,
then it's up to her.

301
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:46,200
We just have to do our best,

302
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:48,960
so she won't be able to insult us.

303
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:56,960
Okay, Mom.

304
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:03,160
I'm well aware what I should do or not do.

305
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:10,880
Get plenty of rest, honey.

306
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,400
- I'm going to bed.
- Okay.

307
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,440
I went to Mook's house today.

308
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:41,080
Mook's house? Why, Ma?

309
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:43,800
Well, I just couldn't stand it,

310
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:47,040
having an ex-daughter-in-law
who's involved in so many scandals.

311
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:51,000
That's good, Ma.
It's time someone said something.

312
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,040
There's news about her
and Mr. Thee every day.

313
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:55,840
I don't really care, but I just feel bad

314
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:58,240
for Kuk's daughter,
for having her as a mom.

315
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:02,840
MOOK

316
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:06,480
Ma, Mook called me.

317
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:08,760
I've got it.

318
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:13,320
Why are you calling your ex?

319
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:14,960
What do you want?

320
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:18,760
It's good that you answered.

321
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:22,800
I wanted to talk to Kuk,
but talking to you directly is better.

322
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:25,600
Just tell me what you want. I'm eating.

323
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,720
I beg of you, from now on,

324
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:31,920
if you're going to talk about me,
come say it to me.

325
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,720
Leave my mom alone.

326
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,120
I don't want her to be upset.

327
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,840
Then behave yourself!

328
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:41,840
Stop acting like a dirty toilet
in front of your house.

329
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,680
I never should've let my son marry you.

330
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:51,240
Hello? Hello?

331
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:56,960
Look at her, hanging up on me like that.

332
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:57,960
Here.

333
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:02,960
How rude! Just you wait.

334
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:05,880
I'll never stop making her life miserable.

335
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:09,000
Damn her for making my son sad.

336
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:10,680
I'll keep going after her.

337
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:32,720
Is something wrong?

338
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:37,040
I see now why Preaw quit.

339
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:53,920
Her leaked video's everywhere online.

340
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:58,640
And worst of all,
someone sent it to our airline.

341
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:02,240
Actually, Preaw got fired,

342
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:04,880
but our airline's hushing it up,
saying she quit on her own.

343
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:10,040
I'm sure this has to do with that Top guy.

344
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:16,520
Scumbag. All you can do is harass women.

345
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:22,679
Khim, where are you going?

346
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:33,360
Screw it. Whatever happens, happens.

347
00:34:51,679 --> 00:34:52,639
Hello, ma'am.

348
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:55,719
Hello. Khim,
can you take me to the hospital?

349
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:58,440
- Is someone hurt?
- Ploy's hospitalized.

350
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,200
What?! What did you say?

351
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,720
Ploy's hospitalized.

352
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:03,480
Let's go.

353
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:12,560
Who did this to you? Tell me.

354
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,520
- There you are, Ma.
- Yes, Top.

355
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:27,840
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

356
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:30,960
Just a small accident, Ma.

357
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:34,560
I didn't call you at first

358
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,520
because I didn't want to scare you.

359
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,320
It's okay.

360
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:41,840
You were clumsy, weren't you?

361
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,560
You're all bruised up.

362
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:47,800
I got lightheaded, Ma,

363
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:52,360
then I fainted and hit a table.

364
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,400
That's how I got this cut on my head.

365
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,720
Are you sure you fell, Ploy?

366
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,080
Why are you asking that?

367
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,800
This is Khim. She's my friend.

368
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:13,600
Is this

369
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:17,560
the friend that came to our wedding,
but left early, like you said?

370
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:25,440
Hello, Ms. Khim.

371
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,320
Nice to meet you.

372
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:32,680
But on our wedding day,

373
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,840
why didn't you stay until the end?

374
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,800
We missed our photo op.

375
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:38,600
What a shame.

376
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:44,680
Anyway, it's good that you're okay.

377
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:48,880
From now on, whatever you do,
please be more careful.

378
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,400
Please don't scold her, Ma.

379
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:55,120
And please don't worry.

380
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:57,680
I'll take good care of her.

381
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:00,600
Okay. Thank you so much

382
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,920
for taking good care of her, Top.

383
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,760
What were you doing, though?

384
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,200
Can I help you?

385
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,680
I was just going to peel her some fruits.

386
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,640
Let me help you then.

387
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:12,760
Sure.

388
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,320
- You can peel the pear.
- Okay.

389
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,240
Are you sure you're okay, Ploy?

390
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:37,280
How are you getting home?

391
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,200
Let me drive you.

392
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,640
It's fine, honey. I can get home myself.

393
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:44,320
You just stay here with Ploy.

394
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,200
Okay.

395
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:51,600
I really am okay. Don't worry.

396
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:54,640
Please drive my mom home.

397
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:02,120
Okay. I'll drive her home.

398
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:08,320
I'll drive you home, Ma.

399
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,880
Okay, honey.

400
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:14,000
Don't take care of her so much
you forget to take care of yourself.

401
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:15,360
You should eat some more.

402
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:17,000
Look at you.

403
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:20,200
You got married not long ago,
and you're already so thin.

404
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,840
Thank you for worrying about me, Ma.

405
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:24,840
I'll take good care of myself,

406
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:27,480
and I'll give you a grandchild soon.

407
00:38:28,120 --> 00:38:29,520
That's good, honey.

408
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:32,000
Here.

409
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,600
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

410
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:42,960
- Let me help you.
- Okay.

411
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,960
Have some, Ploy. I'll be going now.

412
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,120
Okay, Ma.

413
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:59,080
- See you later, Ma.
- See you later.

414
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:01,640
Alright.

415
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:06,600
Please take care of her, Ms. Khim.

416
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,160
Don't be scared.

417
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:36,720
I just wanted to tell you
to get well soon.

418
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:42,240
We'll get to go home soon.

419
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:47,200
Smile a bit.

420
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,440
Please smile.

421
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,960
How cute.

422
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:39,280
This is Mrs. Narin, the chairman
of the board at Narin Beach Resort.

423
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:42,240
Good morning.

424
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,160
You look so familiar, Mr. Thee.

425
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:47,040
Have we met before?

426
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,080
No.

427
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:55,040
Let's not waste time
and get straight to business.

428
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:57,040
Right.

429
00:40:57,840 --> 00:41:01,160
I've briefed Mrs. Narin
on your interest in an investment.

430
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:03,960
She's interested too,
so she wanted to meet you today.

431
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:07,840
I'm happy to hear
you're interested in my small hotel.

432
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:12,400
I learned that your numbers
have gone down by a lot,

433
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:14,440
and you've missed your targets for years.

434
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,280
Why'd you never bring in an investor?

435
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:20,560
Can I ask you this in return?

436
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:24,240
If you know all about our situation,

437
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:27,600
why do you still want
to invest in my hotel?

438
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:32,800
As an investor,

439
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:36,760
once I've assessed
that something is worth it,

440
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:39,000
I'm ready to invest in it.

441
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:40,800
My reason's that simple.

442
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:47,040
Then, we'll wait
for your proposal and contract, Mr. Thee.

443
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,840
But I have just one condition

444
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:53,800
that must be clearly specified
in the contract.

445
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:56,360
You may not fire anyone.

446
00:41:57,320 --> 00:42:00,280
Everyone must remain working here.

447
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:04,400
You sure seem to care
about others, Mrs. Narin.

448
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:10,880
Mr. Pitak,

449
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:14,000
can you run the contract by me
when you're done?

450
00:42:14,600 --> 00:42:15,560
Of course, Mr. Thee.

451
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:19,280
If you'll excuse me.

452
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,560
I hope we'll meet again soon.

453
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,280
He has an urgent meeting.

454
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:56,560
Oh, no! Careful!

455
00:42:57,160 --> 00:42:58,320
Are you okay, ma'am?

456
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Thank you.

457
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:02,600
I'm a little dizzy.
I just need to sit down.

458
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:06,600
Let's go sit outside, then.

459
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:07,640
Here, I'll help you.

460
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:09,320
- Okay. Thank you.
- Just a second.

461
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:14,800
- Thank you.
- Careful, okay?

462
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:16,680
Are you okay? Let's go.

463
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:22,680
- Here's some hot tea.
- Thank you.

464
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:32,760
How are you? Feeling any better?

465
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:37,000
I'm okay now that I got to sit down.

466
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:40,520
You sure you don't need
to go to a hospital?

467
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:44,920
It's fine. It's just how old people are.

468
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,240
Feeling lightheaded
and fainting is normal.

469
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:57,360
<i>Kid, are you okay? Are you hurt?</i>

470
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:00,760
Why'd you stop suddenly?

471
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:03,200
- Are you hurt? You're fine, honey.
- Are you okay?

472
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:04,640
Thank you.

473
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:07,800
I remember now.

474
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:10,520
We met at Narin Beach Resort, didn't we?

475
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,400
I remember you now.

476
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:19,320
You were with your friend.

477
00:44:30,840 --> 00:44:32,080
I'm so sorry.

478
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,800
It really was him.

479
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:38,160
Is something wrong?

480
00:44:40,520 --> 00:44:43,760
It's nothing. I just had a random thought.

481
00:44:47,880 --> 00:44:49,280
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

482
00:44:50,520 --> 00:44:53,280
{\an8}CHADCHAI

483
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:57,240
If you'll excuse me.

484
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,360
I hope we'll meet again,

485
00:44:59,440 --> 00:45:02,080
- Ms.…
- I'm Mook.

486
00:45:02,760 --> 00:45:04,040
Okay, Ms. Mook.

487
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:10,800
Thank you.

488
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,560
Feel free to visit anytime.

489
00:45:17,920 --> 00:45:18,800
Here's mine.

490
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:20,640
Thank you.

491
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:25,440
- If you'll excuse me.
- Sure.

492
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:37,800
"Narin".

493
00:45:40,520 --> 00:45:43,920
I've looked into
Narin Beach Resort, Mr. Thee.

494
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:47,960
The hotel's situation is very severe.

495
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:52,400
Are you sure about investing with them?

496
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:55,000
If their business is doing great,

497
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:58,560
why would they be looking
for an investor, Mr. Pitak?

498
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:03,520
I want to own the business.

499
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:06,000
What do you mean, Mr. Thee?

500
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:08,040
I'll invest with them

501
00:46:08,560 --> 00:46:11,760
as an executive
with a share higher than 80%.

502
00:46:13,760 --> 00:46:17,080
It's almost like
you're taking over the hotel.

503
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,400
Where are we on the contract?

504
00:46:23,640 --> 00:46:26,720
Our legal team is drafting it

505
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:29,120
to cover all the details, like you asked.

506
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:31,200
Once I get it,

507
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:32,800
I'll send it over right away.

508
00:46:37,160 --> 00:46:38,160
Come on in.

509
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:53,440
I brought the revised summary

510
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:56,360
and a rough budget for you to look over.

511
00:46:58,120 --> 00:47:00,160
It's good that you're here. I'm hungry.

512
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:02,560
You're hungry now?

513
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:05,360
It's past lunchtime, you know.

514
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:08,680
Yes, but I had an urgent meeting today,

515
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:10,000
so I haven't eaten at all.

516
00:47:11,360 --> 00:47:15,040
Then, call me when you're done eating.

517
00:47:15,120 --> 00:47:16,440
I'll find a place to wait nearby.

518
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:20,920
I think

519
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:23,680
we should eat during our meeting.

520
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:24,800
I've got another meeting after this.

521
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:28,560
I'll take care of it.

522
00:47:39,520 --> 00:47:41,200
Your food's ready.

523
00:47:48,720 --> 00:47:49,880
Why is there so much food?

524
00:47:49,960 --> 00:47:51,360
When will we be done eating?

525
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,600
Are you messing with me again?

526
00:47:55,440 --> 00:47:58,000
I'm not. I'm just hungry.

527
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:14,360
The other night, you said
you had an important job that came up.

528
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:16,240
How did it go?

529
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:21,880
So deep down, you're worried about me too?

530
00:48:28,400 --> 00:48:31,520
So, can I recharge my energy again?

531
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:32,600
Don't you dare!

532
00:48:32,680 --> 00:48:35,080
If you get closer,
I'm tasing you this time.

533
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:41,720
Let's get started, shall we?

534
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:52,720
As for the work plan, I'm going to revise
for the "Lover: New Normal" campaign,

535
00:48:52,800 --> 00:48:55,880
- I'm going to separate it into--
- Can I miss you still?

536
00:49:00,440 --> 00:49:03,280
You can, but there's no point.

537
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:05,320
You'll only waste your time.

538
00:49:10,200 --> 00:49:12,240
Can I continue?

539
00:49:16,560 --> 00:49:18,520
Okay, as I said,

540
00:49:18,600 --> 00:49:21,600
for the work plan,
I have a plan A and a plan B.

541
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:22,680
Okay.

542
00:49:24,560 --> 00:49:25,400
Mr. Thee.

543
00:49:29,880 --> 00:49:32,120
This is all of plan A.

544
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:35,240
But I might have to ask your hotel
for more information…

545
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:38,000
Just a little bit, okay?

546
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:41,480
And then, this is all of plan B.

547
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:44,400
I'm going to make gift vouchers.

548
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:47,240
And for the couples
who want to go on a honeymoon,

549
00:49:47,320 --> 00:49:49,560
I'll send a letter
with their map attached--

550
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,040
Stay focused.

551
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:03,920
Pick whichever one you like.

552
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:06,720
- But for--
- What was plan A again?

553
00:50:06,800 --> 00:50:10,600
For plan A, I will attach this
along with it for them.

554
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:29,920
Thank you for driving me, Khim.

555
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:36,880
Don't worry, Ma.

556
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:39,320
I'll help take care of Ploy.

557
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:40,800
Thank you.

558
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:43,240
You and Mook are the only ones

559
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:46,800
who've taken care of Ploy
since she was in school.

560
00:50:47,440 --> 00:50:49,360
Ploy is too soft.

561
00:50:50,040 --> 00:50:51,880
She can't keep up with anyone.

562
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:56,160
She's lucky to have
a great husband like Top.

563
00:50:56,880 --> 00:50:58,840
Stay close like this, okay?

564
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:00,160
Don't ever leave each other.

565
00:51:01,480 --> 00:51:02,320
Of course, Ma.

566
00:51:02,920 --> 00:51:04,600
- I'll head inside now.
- Okay.

567
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:07,840
- See you later, Ma.
- See you later.

568
00:51:29,560 --> 00:51:30,760
Come meet me.

569
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:34,360
What an unfamiliar place to meet.

570
00:51:36,240 --> 00:51:38,160
Why not a hotel room like last time?

571
00:51:39,880 --> 00:51:41,240
What did you do to Ploy?

572
00:51:41,320 --> 00:51:43,760
Why is she at the hospital?

573
00:51:43,840 --> 00:51:46,600
And what happened to Preaw
was your doing, right?

574
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:56,800
I already told you,
whoever doesn't obey me

575
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:00,160
or doesn't understand me

576
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:04,400
will need to get punished.

577
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:09,120
You're not a real man.

578
00:52:10,520 --> 00:52:11,960
All you can do is hurt people.

579
00:52:12,720 --> 00:52:13,560
You monster.

580
00:52:21,520 --> 00:52:22,960
You want that treatment too?

581
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:28,080
Think you can do whatever to me
just because you have the video?

582
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:35,200
I only wanted to meet you today

583
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:40,960
to tell you that I'm not scared

584
00:52:42,160 --> 00:52:45,600
that you'll do to me
what you did to Preaw.

585
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:53,800
I'll expose everything,
so everyone knows just how evil you are.

586
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:04,880
What's this about, Prao?

587
00:53:06,680 --> 00:53:08,760
You said we're taking our son on a trip.

588
00:53:11,680 --> 00:53:15,000
Well, since we're back home,

589
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:17,520
I invited my dad to have dinner with us.

590
00:53:18,840 --> 00:53:21,680
Poonpun hasn't seen
his grandpa for over a year.

591
00:53:21,760 --> 00:53:22,920
You haven't either.

592
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:25,320
Then what about the others?

593
00:53:26,560 --> 00:53:29,320
Those are local politicians, aren't they?

594
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:35,720
- Hello, Dad.
- Hi, honey.

595
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,080
Hello, Dad.

596
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:39,600
It sure has been a while, son-in-law.

597
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:47,400
Poonpun! You're already this tall?

598
00:53:47,480 --> 00:53:50,200
Has it really been that long
since I saw him?

599
00:53:52,240 --> 00:53:54,200
Come to Grandpa, Poonpun. Come on.

600
00:53:55,120 --> 00:53:57,520
Come on. Come here.

601
00:53:58,560 --> 00:54:00,240
You've grown so much, handsome.

602
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:03,200
Study hard, okay?

603
00:54:03,280 --> 00:54:06,760
So when you graduate,
you can come work with me.

604
00:54:06,840 --> 00:54:07,680
Which ministry do you want?

605
00:54:08,560 --> 00:54:10,080
Come on, tell me.

606
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:14,800
The Ministry of Magic,
like in <i>Harry Potter</i>.

607
00:54:14,880 --> 00:54:17,240
Oh? Ministry of Magic?

608
00:54:18,120 --> 00:54:20,600
Sure, I'll set it up for you.

609
00:54:21,120 --> 00:54:22,280
Are you hungry? Let's go.

610
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:24,760
Let's go inside and eat together.

611
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:27,360
Let's go.

612
00:54:27,440 --> 00:54:28,400
Let's go.

613
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:36,360
It's just dinner. Don't be so serious.

614
00:54:36,880 --> 00:54:38,840
It's normal for politicians.

615
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:41,440
They have to meet once in a while.

616
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:44,520
You have to get to know them too,

617
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:46,240
for your own future.

618
00:54:47,640 --> 00:54:50,200
We've gone over this so many times, Prao.

619
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:54,800
Go eat with your dad.

620
00:54:55,320 --> 00:54:56,800
I'll pick you up when you're done.

621
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:27,040
Yes, Dad.

622
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:29,680
I'll go home by myself.

623
00:56:29,760 --> 00:56:31,800
Don't send anyone to bother me.

624
00:56:32,320 --> 00:56:33,480
Okay?

625
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:53,400
Are you okay?

626
00:56:57,400 --> 00:56:59,280
- Do you have a car?
- Huh?

627
00:57:02,320 --> 00:57:03,200
Hey!

628
00:57:06,960 --> 00:57:08,200
{\an8}Mr. Thee!

629
00:57:12,040 --> 00:57:14,680
{\an8}Mr. Thee! Kongkwan!

630
00:57:14,760 --> 00:57:16,560
{\an8}If you go missing,

631
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,880
{\an8}what would Mommy and Grandma do?

632
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:26,920
{\an8}You should know
what you're supposed to do.

633
00:57:27,640 --> 00:57:29,880
{\an8}You can't get distracted like this.

634
00:57:30,400 --> 00:57:32,120
{\an8}And about Veluree too.

635
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:33,320
{\an8}You--

636
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:43,840
{\an8}Let me help you.

637
00:58:35,280 --> 00:58:37,560
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

